msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getpass/index.rst:79
msgid "Using getpass Without a Terminal"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/getpass/index.rst:81
msgid "Under Unix, ``getpass()`` always requires a tty it can control via :mod:`termios`, so input echoing can be disabled. This means values will not be read from a non-terminal stream redirected to standard input. Instead, ``getpass`` tries to get to the tty for a process, and no error is raised if they can access it."
msgstr ""

